    {
      "source": "evaluator",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:\n\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n}\n\nany idea why it's overlapping on small screens?"
    },
    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the overlapping issue is a common problem when dealing with mobile displays. It sounds like your product image and title are having a bit of a squabble, but don't worry, we can sort it out. \n\nFirst, let's make sure your product image isn't too large. You might want to try adding a max-width property to the .product-image class. This will ensure that the image doesn't stretch too far, causing the title to overlap. Something like this:\n\n```css\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n  max-width: 300px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n}\n```\n\nNext, let's ensure there's enough breathing room between your image and title. You can add a bottom margin to the .product-image class to give it some space. Try this:\n\n```css\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n  max-width: 300px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  margin-bottom: 20px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n}\n```\n\nNow, let's see if that helps your product title find its place. If the issue persists, it might be worth checking out your theme's responsive settings or consulting with a Shopify expert.",
